# 📢 Subnet Announcement 📢

We are excited to share an important update from the subnet team.

The validator has officially started sending organic requests. At this stage, only one validator (UID 0) is actively sending these requests, but soon, all four verified validators will begin participating.

### Here’s how it works:
Each validator sends an organic request to top 10 miners, and both the miners and the requests are non-overlapping. This means that once all four validators are active, they will collectively send 40 unique tasks to the top 40 miners, ensuring full task diversity across the network.
We are continuously working on building a reliable system with real-world applications by this organic requests handling structure. We will keep you updated on our progress.

To boost miners handle these organic requests correctly:

The video clips used in these organic requests will range from 1 to 5 seconds in duration.

**Please note**: The website functionality related to organic requests is currently disabled, and will be re-enabled once miner performance stabilizes with this update.

Only way is to change the concept completely. In any setup where more miners = more income, you will see competition for UIDs, where those that have the upper hand (e.g. >100 UIDs) can afford to keep reg price high, as a barrier to entry. They keep everybody out and they don't even have to be good at their work anymore, because who can afford to compete, starting from scratch, for >1 tao per UID...

At the current rate you need roughly 4 days to earn back the reg fee. That means you have to not only have a decent miner, but you also have to achieve the threshold within a day, and they stay above the threshold for three more days, and not have your mining infra crash. So now you're not only doing AI but also HA & devops...

The way it can work is to have a steep incentive curve: say only 5 miners earn significant income, that leaves >200 slots for aspiring miners. Buying them all would be unnecessary and wasteful, and not even that useful, because the competing miner would only need one UID. We've seen this setup work in LLM training subnets, and currently in SN68 where they suffered an issue where more UIDs would increase chances; they changed the setup so that having more than 5 UIDs is useless, and the reg fee immediately dropped to almost zero, see graph.
